content.description: Climb straight up past small but positive pebbles (crux) and eventually through jugs over a bulge.
content.protection: Top rope, use the 5th staple down; recommend webbing/cord to extend over cliff edge. This route now has 6 bolts.
content.location:
Sunset Slab North

Start on the right side of the large pine tree/moss patch.

climbs.name: Pick Pockets
climbs.fa: B. Middleton, J. Whidden, D. Kloke

content.description: Begin climbing the face immediately left of the gouge, up and over a 6-inch overhang past 4 bolts to chain anchors
content.location: third bolted line from the left

content.description: Second route from the left on the South Slab.  Start right of the fir tree on lightly featured, polished slab.  Climb past 4 bolts to chain anchors.
content.location: chain anchors shared with Syd the Sloth and Pick Pockets
3rd top rope route from the left. The staples aren't aligned with the routes. The book depicts set up top rope from the 4th or 5th staple from the left.

content.description: Slab. Listed as a 5.7+ but feels like a 5.6.
content.protection: 6 bolts. Recommend using the Sojo Mojo staple anchor and add directional at last bolt for TR.
content.location: To the right of The Stinger crack.

content.description:
A good route for adding variety if tired of slab.

Follow the obvious chunky groove to a large niche, finishing with a jug haul over the bulge. Has some nice locks/jams, but definitely 'interesting' for gear (or lack thereof).
content.protection: Gear to 1", giant staple; use 7th staple down for TR, recommend webbing/cord to extend over edge.
content.location: Right end of Sunset Slab North.

content.description:
Climb on left side of first two bolts through the polished rock and onto small but highly textured knobs and edges. Finishes with a jug haul through the bulge.

Variation: 5.10a, stay right of first two bolts on the dark colored rock.
content.protection: 6 bolts, giant staple; use 6th staple down if setting a TR, recommend webbing/cord to extend over edge.
content.location:
Sunset Slab North

Start at obvious reddish/tan polished section of rock right of large pine tree.
